@node req "Requires"

    @{u}Software requirements: @{uu}
     - MUI v3.8 by Stefan Stuntz
     - AmiTCP or compatible TCP/IP stack (based on bsdsocket.library)

    @{u}MCC requirements: @{uu}
     - Betterstring.mcc
     - Lamp.mcc
     - Newstring.mcc
     - Transferanim.mcc

                             @{b}@{u}All the MCC's are copyrighted by several coders @{uu}@{ub}

    @{u}Other requirements: @{uu}
     - Sense of humor :-)
     - Lot of numbers to play with.

@endnode

@node int "Instruction"

  Welcome to @{b}SmsEngineer@{ub}

  a simple tool to send sms. It was developed mainly for personal usage and to cut
  our gsm's  bill costs  :).
  Then you know, we uploaded to aminet to make it available for all the users around
  the world :) and we got lot of regs...

  This was enough for us to continue supporting and develop it.

  
  @{u}happy sms sending !@{uu}

  And don't forget to ask for you registration :-) [cause it's @{fg fill}free@{fg text} ]

@endnode

@node Ins "How to install SmsEngineer"

   Well nothing can be easier...

   You can of course use the standard installer wich will make all the work for you.

   Instead if you're a linux kernel hacker, a master of coding or simply hate the installer, 
   you can do it by hands... Just make a dir called smsengineer and put the exe file
   and all of its configs to it. Copy also the catalogs to locale directory.

   That's all now

@endnode

@node cfg "Configuration"

  You can use the prefs from smsengineer or use 

   .----------------------.
   |TOOLTYPES PREFERENCES:|
   `----------------------´

    Default Number

      Tooltype command : DefNumber
      Example          : DefNumber=1234567
      To use for       : Set a default number

    Default Text

      Tooltype command : DefText
      Example          : DefText=I am Online!
      To use for       : Set a default send text

    Default Signatur

      Tooltype command : DefSign
      Example          : DefSign=SMSEngineerMUI
      To use for       : Set a default Signatur wich is be the one
                         wich is be shown in the GUI

    InfoWindow

      Tooltype command : InfoWindow
      Commands         : ON  - Start with intro
                         OFF - Start without intro
      Example          : InfoWindow=off
      To use for       : Put Start intro on and off

    Nation

      Tooltype command : Nation
      Commands         : 1 - xx
      Example          : Nation = 14 (Germany)
      To use for       : With this you can set up the Nation cycle on
                         startup

    Prefix

      Tooltype command : Prefix
      Commands         : 1 - xx
      Example          : Prefix = 3 (On Germany = 0171)
      To use for       : With this you can set up the Prefix cycle on
                         startup

   Server

      Tooltype command : Server
      Commands         : 1 - xx
      Example          : Server = 5 (E-Loft)
      To use for       : With this you can set up the Server cycle on
                         startup

   Signatur

      Tooltype command : SGNx (x = 1 - 10)
      Example          : SGN1 = dEFToNE
      To use for       : Set up your default signatures for the
                         Listview
   SignPos

      Tooltype command : SignPos
      Commands         : START  - Signature on Start
                         END    - Signature on End
                         NOSIGN - No Signature
      Example          : SignPos = START (SIGNATUR: message)
      To use for       : Set up the Position of the Signature
                        

     ## TOOLTYPES ONLY WORKS IN THE FULL VERSION ##

@endnode

@node h2u "How to use"

   Ok.. First of all u want to know how to personalize to your own need smseng ?
   If so go to @{"configuration..." link cfg}

   Ok hope you know how to activate a program ;-), now you'll get a window
   in front of you full of buttons...

   SmsEngineer use mui bubble help, so if you need an help on a particular gadget
   leave the mouse pointer over it and the bubble will pop up (refer to mui documentation
   for how to activate bubble)

   The first row of buttons are SEND (send current message)
                                ABOUT (info about the program)
                                QUIT  (guess it ?)
   on the left side you'll note a field called SIGNATURE. Here you can write the
   text that should be tagged to you sms or use the left popupgadget to select from a list
   (the list of signature is user-definable... refer to @{"configuration" link cfg})

   Under this we get the field MESSAGE (here you can write the full sms message)

   Under you'll see the remaining chars gadget wich show how much chars you can still write in sms.

   And then you've to enter the gsm number. This is done by selecting the country and
   then the local prefix. After them add the gsmnumber to the NUMBER field.

   So if you've to send a sms to an italian boy/girl wich used wind (0328) :

   Select ITALY on the nation cycle, then 0328 on the local prefix and write the number
   to NUMBER gadget

   ITALY 0328 1234567

    @{b}NOTE@{ub} plz don't flood people with your sms. In some countryes reciving sms
    in not free :-(

@endnode

@node reg "Registration"

   What ? Is this program shareware ?

   We know that coding is done just for fun and this is the spirit behind
   smsengineer. So if you want to receive your keyfile, just start the
   smsregister program and send us the generated form via email and
   you get your personal keyfile.



   See @{"Authors" link con} for addresses

   As we're still working on it and we plan to make it really use
   comfortable for the user and nice, we need your help. If you know any
   others gateway plz mail us them.

   Let us know the critics and the compliment cause we want to develop
   something you like ! We'll try to implement as much as we can.

   This software is subject to the "Standard Amiga FD-Software Copyright Note".
   It is MAILWARE as defined in paragraph 4b.
   If you like it and use it regularly please send use the register form
   and you will get your personal keyfile ...
   For more information please read "@{"AFD-COPHYRIGHT" link dis}" (Version 1.4 or higher).

@endnode

@node sup "Support"

   All the support info, should be gained directly from the blitzengineer's
   mailing list. The list is keep in 3 languages ENGLISH, GERMAN and ITALIAN.

   How to Join:
   Send a empty email to bengineers-subscribe@egroups.com and you will get all
   the infos you need.

   Rules:
   The mailinglist is just for those user which want to communicate
   about problems, info, news and all the other nice things for
   smsengineer. @{b}Spam is absolutely proibhited @{ub}!

   you can also get in touch with us. See @{"Authors" link con}

    If you know a particular gateway that is not supported by the program, you
    can report it to us and we'll try to add to the program.

@endnode

@node his "History"

@{b}@{u}HISTORY:@{uu}@{ub}

            v1.o.7  PrefsPageGUI is finishd and it works! :)
                    Added Croatian catalog
                    Fixed catalog .cd filez for prefs


            v1.o.6  Sixth Aminet Preview
                    ***Fixed Bug! Now the Prefix tooltype work :)
                    ***Fixed Bug! Now the chars free works now correctly
                    Added Listview for the comming soon adress book
                    Few internal changes
                    New tooltype to setup the position of the signature
                    Signature will not be displayed when SignPos$=NOSIGN
 		    ***Fixed Bug! CharsFree works now with the gateway.dat
                    Changed Output From CharsFree
                    

            v1.o.5  Fifth Aminet Preview
                    Changed a little bit the GUI
                    Added new tooltype to setup the default Signatur
                    ***Fixed Bug! Now the signatur will be sended too

            v1.o.4
                    Fourth Aminet Preview
                    Rewrite the catalog stuff for 100% of translation

            v1.o.3
                    Third Aminet Preview
                    Added new tooltype to setup the cycles positions
                    Added new tooltype to start with(out) intro
                    Added new toolbar
                    Added Signatur PopListView. Many user request this :)
                    Added Tooltype to change the Signatur files
                    Add AFD-COPYRIGHT (English, German)
            v1.o.2
                    Second Aminet Preview
                    Add the new Register programm

            v1.o.1
                    First Aminet Preview
                    Add new GSM servers to a extra file
                    Add three Bars to GUI
                    Change SMSMaster Image To SMSEngineer Logo :)
                    Change text.mcc for informations to infotext.mcc
                    Added tooltype for defaultnumber
                    Added tooltype for defaulttext
                    Added Toolbar do not work now :(

            v1.o.o
                    First Internal Version

    And here is the darkside of development of smsengineer... It was started just
    for personal usage for sending sms to friends... the first version was a simple
    Gadgtools gui with support for freesms server. After that freesms server was
    hacked (yeah it was quite funny coming back home on the 1st jan and see "xxxx
    was here!" written on freesms page :-) Nice work whoever you are :-) )
    We started to support more gateways and the serious development started.

    The first working version of smsengineer was dated 10-oct-99.

@endnode

