@node sms "What is an sms ?"

 Ok let's go into tech... Sms stand for Short Message System. Sms are little
 text message sended to gsm phone. There are also phones who can send picture
 messages... We don't know anything about them cause we don't have that gsm.
 If you can supply further info about that format, plz contact us.

 Sms are usually sended and received by two gsm phones. Another way to send
 sms is using internet gateways and this what smsengineer do.

 Sms sended by gsm phones can consist of up to 160 chars, but usually sms from
 internet are shorter due to server adverts.

 How can you know if another person get your sms ?

 No way ! Sometimes sms (from gsm) are delivered almost immediately (3, 4 mins
 delay) but other time they will take up to 24 hours to be delivered... :-(

 This is caused by several cause.. lack of field, lack of free band from the
 operator. For sms from internet the situation is even worse... Someday all sms
 are delivered other days none. So you can't used sms for importand messagge :
 "Would you like to marry me" or things like that !

@endnode

